<br />
That seems bizarre given the ton of improvements over the past few months. Are you saying pet zoning is something the mage community has never requested? The community never asked for the pet tanking changes?
<br />

<br />
As to why anyone would start a mage these days - mages are in extremely good shape apart from the very high end. And, do you know what, not everyone LIKES the very high end 50+ man raiding game, or groups with Qvic+ guilds. I have had a wiz for 4 years but seeing as I could literally count the number of raids I have done on one hand if I had my time over again a mage would have been a much better choice. Yet my playstyle is probably in the majority - this board is extremely unrepresentative of all EQ players believe it or not..
<br />

<br />
Besides, SOE (and Verant before them) are notorious for over-improving the perceived weaker classes and it wouldnt suprise me in the least if mages ended up ruling the top end as well as the middle ground before EQ's run is over.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
